整理資料

先將所需的SPDF檔讀進來，再將其中會用到的雙北地區資料挑出來。

my_spdf=readOGR( dsn= getwd() , layer="TOWN_MOI_1061130") 
## OGR data source with driver: ESRI Shapefile

## with 368 features
## It has 7 fields
my_spdf@bbox
##        min       max
## x 118.1437 124.56115
## y  21.8956  26.38528
df1<-my_spdf[my_spdf@data$COUNTYID=="F", ]
df2<-my_spdf[my_spdf@data$COUNTYID=="A", ]
df3<-rbind(df1,df2)

開始作圖

雙北不分科目家教薪資平均與平均所得比較

all <- read_csv("money_vs_region_list.csv", col_names = "all")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   all = col_double()
## )
all$all<-as.numeric(all$all)
df3@data<-cbind(df3@data,all)

ave_salary <- read_csv("所得_new.csv", col_names = "ave_salary")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   ave_salary = col_integer()
## )
df3@data<-cbind(df3@data,ave_salary)
df3@data$ave_salary<-as.numeric(df3@data$ave_salary)


choroLayer(spdf = df3, df = df3@data, var = "ave_salary",legend.pos = "none")
cols <- carto.pal(pal1 = "green.pal", n1 = 2, pal2 = "red.pal", n2 = 4)
choroLayer(spdf = df3, df = df3@data, var = "ave_salary", 
            col = cols, 
           border = "grey40", lwd = 0.5,  
           legend.title.txt = "average salary\nfor each distinct", 
           legend.values.rnd = 2, add = TRUE)
plot(df3, border = "grey20", lwd = 0.75, add = TRUE)

propSymbolsLayer(spdf = df3, df = df3@data, 
                 var = "all",inches =0.5 , symbols = "bar", col = "yellow",
                 legend.pos = "right", legend.title.txt = "tutor average\nsalary", 
                 legend.style = "c")
## Warning in st_centroid.sfc(st_geometry(x), of_largest_polygon =
## of_largest_polygon): st_centroid does not give correct centroids for
## longitude/latitude data
